Beatrice Shongwe, News24 CorrespondentThree Rondavels, Mpumalanga. (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Graskop - A tourist from Gauteng died when he fell down a 100m cliff at the Three Rondavels mountain top near Graskop, Mpumalanga police said on Monday.&nbsp;Sergeant Gerald Sedibe said the man fell to his death after going through a demarcated area at the world-renowned tourist destination on Saturday afternoon.Police and emergency services retrieved his body on Sunday afternoon around 17:00. The man had not yet been identified, but was estimated to be aged 34.Sedibe warned the public to adhere to the rules and stay within demarcated areas at tourist attractions.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.